news.title: West Bengal to appoint IAS officers for monitoring PMAY funds
news.para: The Centre last month cleared Rs 584 crore under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) after keeping funds pending due to a nomenclature controversy and alleged misuse of money.

news.title: Bengaluru: Over 60 RWAs demand a plan to fix infrastructure in 15 days
news.para: The letter spoke about the various issues schoolchildren and office-goers face daily

news.title: Kolkata civic body extends deadline for UAA switchover to end of month
news.para: ​KMC on Monday set a December-end deadline for property tax payers to make the switch, failing which, the civic body will unilaterally make the conversion and impose an annual penalty of 5%.

news.title: Kanpur: 340 residents declared lucky winners in lottery of plots
news.para: For 371 plots for the economically weaker sections of the society, KDA had asked the aspirants to submit duly filled forms through Axis Bank. According to S B Rai, public relations officer, for 371 plots, KDA received around 825 applications.

news.title: Two builders, estate officer held for property fraud in Haryana
news.para: The two builders were identified as Rishiraj and Vashisht Kumar Goyal, while the estate officer is Mukesh Kumar Solanki. The move followed a complaint that the vigilance bureau received against Rishiraj, the director of RR Foundation Engineering, and Solanki in 2019.

news.title: Bombay HC seeks govt, SRA's reply on inclusion of nature park in Dharavi project
news.para: A division bench of Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice Abhay Ahuja was hearing a public interest litigation (PIL) claiming that the Mahim Nature Park, which is a protected forest, has been unlawfully included in the redevelopment of Dharavi, Asia's largest slum.

news.title: NCLT rejects claims of foul play in insolvency of Radius Estates
news.para: Debenture holders of the company led by ICICI Prudential and Beacon Trusteeship had approached NCLT with a plea to turn down Adani Good Homes' offer for Radius Estates claiming the company had violated the bidding conditions.

news.title: Centre likely to strengthen recovery mechanism to rein in errant builders
news.para: The issue of non-compliance by builders came for discussion at a recently held meeting of a sub-committee headed by Union housing secretary Manoj Joshi.

news.title: County Group buys 28 acre land in Noida for about Rs 450 crore
news.para: County Group recently bought the 28-acre land parcels, which belonged to realty firm Ambience group. Indiabulls Housing Finance has sold this land to recover its loan from the Ambience Group.

news.title: Noida: Society asks bachelor tenants to vacate, says PGs being run in violation of rule
news.para: ​The residential body of the posh society in Sector 93A said they had been getting complaints from other residents because of which notices have been issued to those living as paying guests (PGs).

news.title: You will soon have access to paperless home loans
news.para: In addition to digital documentation, what has made online lending possible for banks is the availability of data — both structured & unstructured — and credit scores.

news.title: Kochi corporation seeks tax for building pulled down 13 years ago
news.para: Kochi corporation officials have sent notice to the owner of a building, which was demolished 13 years ago, to pay building tax till date. The owner had pulled down his house and built a new house in the same location.

news.title: CBI moves Delhi HC challenging statutory bail granted to DHFL promoters
news.para: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has challenged a trial court's December 3 order granting statutory bail to Wadhawan brothers due to "incomplete charge sheet".

news.title: WeWork leases 50,000 sq ft to National Australia Bank in Gurugram
news.para: National Australia Bank employs around 32,000 people, supporting more than eight-and-a-half million customers in Australia. A majority of its financial service businesses operate in Australia and New Zealand, with other businesses located in Asia, the UK and the US.

news.title: Now, ED begins probe into land grab cases in Goa, may invoke PMLA
news.para: Goa police has submitted documents on the ED’s request. Police said that all the documents related to the FIRs have been given to the ED.
